,Recommended,260650,10913375,"Posted: 28 June, 2014",all,Poofie Love bird,"Splintercell, Death to spies, Velvet assasin fans all need a coy of this game!Pros:-The story is short and sweet! You do not need to care about your guy, you are a CIA assassin!- For a 2005 game this has some really good animation and asthetics. The models are very human like, and have a lot of personality.- AI is very smart. No aimlessly running into things. They seek cover, or seek you and attack.-Hard core reaslism! No standing there as they riddle you with round after round. If you get shot, YOU  GET SHOT! Stealth is the key.-Guns are very realistic too. None of this ""snipe with my handgun crap lilke in splintercel. Tou need to be really close to use a handgun, just like in real life. Stealth is the key to this game.-Levels are very well made. Trees are animates. Lights and ambient sounds are all there.- Great post processing for 2005! You get a MSAA like AA in this game by default! very nice looking atmosphere.CONS:it is from 2005, Yes you will need to play it in 4:3 aspect ratio, but it has so much character you will not careThis is not some crappy console port, expect to play with your full keyboard. Xbox and other controller ,Controls can be used but Mouse and Keyboard are essential in the few times you need to make snap shots.Conclusion:10/10, For a 2005 game, and a ""GIVEAWAY"" pricetag in the steam summer sale, I say this is a MUST buy! (even if you dont like stealth games it is really good)"
